{
  "stem": "717.1",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "We didn't know what was going on in Russia at that time.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Before the war, I'm talking about.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Before 1937, when we started hearing all the good things about the killing of all the, the pioneers of the revolution.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Yeah, there were constant discussions always.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "That's all I remember, constant.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Even-- when I had a birthday, that's we-- every year, even though we weren't rich, my parents made a party for my birthday.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And of course, all the kids got together.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And then later on, the grown-ups came.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And there were always discussion, until the kids started rebelling.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "This is our party.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "No discussions.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "But there were always, always political discussion.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "They wanted to change the world.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "They wanted to make a revolution, the fascist Poland.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And of course, there was plenty to talk about with the persecution and Poland against the Jews.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "I never had any Polish friends.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "It's impossible to believe now-- living in the United States 30 years and then 15 years in Australia before that-- to live in a country, which is predominantly Gentile, and not to have any Gentile kids friends.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "I lived-- we lived in a building, there were maybe three or four Jewish families.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "The rest were Gentiles.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "They had kids.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "I never had any Polish friends.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] It's impossible now.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "It boggles the mind.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "I can't understand how that would be possible.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "And we weren't newcomers in Poland.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "We had lived there 1,000 years.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] It was, I think, a self-imposed segregation.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, yes, constantly.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We were scared of the-- we walked down the street, used to call us [NON-ENGLISH], filthy Jew.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "That-- all that was a constant.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "That was a thing that was an everyday-- it was part of the life, our life.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
